article.headline: UVSC 83
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Ryan Toolson scored 20 points to lead Utah Valley State to an 83-56 win over South Dakota State on Saturday night. The Wolverines (19-7) seized control of the game midway through the first half with a 12-0 run that ended with a 28-14 lead over the Jackrabbits (5-21). Reserve guard Josh Olsen sparked the rally with a jump shot, 3-pointer, steal and assist. UVSC forward Richard Troyer scored 10 of his 12 points in the second half as the Wolverine lead steadily increased. Troyers free throws in the final minute gave UVSC its largest lead of the night at 27 points. Toolson finished 7-of-11 from the field, including 4-for-7 on 3-pointers. Chris Bailey had 13 points and five assists for the Wolverines. Kai Williams had 20 points and 10 rebounds for S. Dakota St. The Jackrabbits out-rebounded UVSC 41-26, but shot 38.5 percent from the field compared to 56 percent for the Wolverines.
